I'd like to add the feature of recording games 

this feature should have the following shape:
- the host records the game
- the host records the game when they decide to "stop game" after the prompt "are you sure you want to stop the game" is affirmed
- there is a "game settings" toggle that only the host can change for recording games. it is on by default and if disabled has the current behavior (before the following changes)
- games played with a secret deck cannot be recorded and therefore will skip the rest of all of this. that is since secret deck and record game are mutually exclusive they should gray each-other out when either is on (though certainly both can be off) 
- remember that secret deck is only visible to the host, but this record game toggle is visible to everyone 
- after they affirm that they want to stop the game, a window pops up which asks which team won the game (showing either the Good.webp alligence or Evil.webp alligence). They should both be dimmed until the user picks one, then it turns full color, only one can be selected, but they can switch between until they leave this dialogue (see next point). this is required for the host to dismiss this 
- below the previous question, asks the user to provide a "hostSecret" ideally this can work with the browser like a password (so maybe calling it a password field or something) so that it auto-fills out for those who have already created one. this secret is required for "detailed record" which we'll talk about in a moment, but importantly not required for the regular option (Dismiss) (but is still nice to have). this hostSecret helps me later surface games to users/hosts who know this password. that way usernames and cookiesessions are not tied to users. this hostSecret will sit in plaintext on the server (along with the rest of the record which I will outline).
- after that is those two options alluded too earlier, (1) Create Detailed Game Record and (2) Dismiss
- Dismiss will get rid of all dialogues and send a request to the server to record the  game which involves writing the hostSecret (or undefined since not required if the box is equal to the empty string), the entire game server state as a JSON object, and the new piece of data "winningTeam", all to a file (which is in the gitignore) which serves as a database. this file should basically store an array of json objects. I forgot to mention it should also include the time it took from pressing Start Game to pressing "confirm End game". (or actually just include both time stamps and also duration) Since this a personal project, I don't currently plan on using a database for this. perhaps design for easy addition later (or if you think I really should be using a database, tell me this before getting started)
- Create Detailed Game Record, will do all of that above stuff, but not before asking for a detailed record of the game in a new dialogue (which I will outline momentarily). This new data is all manpulated in client state all the way up until the new dialogue is dismissed with "submit". You should not be able to escape this dialogue before pressing submit and submit should have ways to tell the user (just like above with not selecting the winning team) that the dialogue is incomplete. 

detailed game record outline: there are up to 5 leaders in a game that lead (up to 5) "quests" that can "fail" or "succeed". the App already understands who the first leader is and therefore this should already be filled out (and uneditable). it should ask for the next 4 leaders and the result of each of the 5 missions. this is done by having each row as "Quest 1: " <LEADER SELECTOR HTML DROPDOWN> <Good.webp> <Bad.webp> where, the drop down should be big enough for people on a phone to select from the drop down and, just like the previous diaglogue, only one of the two images can be non-grayed out at a time. these conditions must be met for submission of this part to be allowed: it must be that the quests are completed in order without gaps (i.e. quest 2 always occurs in games where quest 3 happens and quest 1 always occurs). one team (either evil or good) must have 3 quests of their color (its a game of 3 of 5, otherwise the user is attempting to submit an invalid game). note that no person can be a leader twice, so gray out (but don't remove) dropdown of people who are already selected as leader (or the following amulet thing described below)

further, after these row selections there are "amulets" (game_pieces/Amulet.webp game_pieces/Faded_Amulet.webp) of which there can be 3 in a game (and 3 faded). note that faded amulets and amulets are not the same but are importantly related. amulets are mutually exclusive with leadership, so just like leadership is mutally exclusive with leadership, do the same gray-out for those already selected with amulet or leadership. those who can be selected by faded amulet are anyone who is not already selected by amulet or faded amulet. that is someone can recieve an amulet if they already have a faded amulet earlier, but not the inverse. make sure to also gray on these rules. these amulets are also done in order (1 before 2 before 3, it can be the case that no amulets occur), this condition should be checked on submission. like leadership, there should be 3 rows, each row will have an amulet image and then person dropdown and to the right a faded amulet and another person dropdown. 

finally, in the case that 3 leaderships were won by evil an option should appear that is two buttons called ("End Game Branch") between two buttons "Pointing Phase" and "Blind Hunter Phase" where exactly one can be selected for submission, the form only allows one to be pressed at a time, and the both start un pressed. 

after all of this is a green submit button. 